         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne botanic &amp; zoological Garden ¶ 4 February 1861. ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honor to inform you, that the papers transmitted to me in reference to fixing an appropriate scale of rations for the Cam...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">61.02.04</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Moore</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">S61/999, unit 749, VPRS 1189/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS written<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by Carl Wilhelmi and signed by M. See also M to J. Moore, 25 January 1861.</p>
               </note>Melbourne botanic &amp; zoological Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">4 February 1861.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to inform you, that the papers transmitted to me in reference to fixing an appropriate scale of rations for the Camels at the Royal Park, were laid before the Committee of the zoological Garden at the monthly meeting on the 1 February, when I was instructed to submit to you such a schedule as the available information might suggest.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>After due enquiry at Cremorne<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Cremorne Gardens, Richmond, Vic.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and at the Royal Park it appears, that</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">4lb of Grain</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">2lb of Bran</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">3 ounces of Salt and</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">16lb of hay, or what would be preferable a proportionate quantity of green feed in lieu of the latter, would form under ordinary circumstances a suitable daily ration for each camel, which supply however would require occasional modification according to the state of the health &amp; condition of the animals in various seasons, crushed wheat being for instance at times desirable in lieu of grain.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reference to the rations for the attendent it would perhaps simplify arrangements in allowing him a small remuneration (from 1/6 to 2/6 per diem) instead of rations, if the man should be quite abstemious or be under such control as to render his obtaining spirits unlikely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your most obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Mr Undersecretary Moore.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 7 February 1861, Moore<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>annotated the file: 'The Exploration Committee having declined the further charge of these Camels they must now be considered as belonging to the Govt Zoological Collection and Dr Mueller will be so good as to provide for their future care and maintenance accordingly'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to R. Heales, 19 February 1861,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and M to J. Moore, 12 April 1861<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 61-04-12a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
